{
  "texts": [
    "F(X) represent the residual mapping that must be acquired during the learning process, σ is the correction unit, W 1 and W 2 are the weights for each layer, and F(X)+X is the output of the residual module.The use of residual structures in deep learning has revolutionized the traditional approach by allowing direct mapping of input data to output while maintaining a constant residual connection.",
    "This approach prevents the loss of information during the transfer process.",
    "In the context of scene classification, when the difference between image categories is minimal, the model requires in-depth learning of image features to achieve accurate classification.",
    "However, when the difference between image categories is significant, shallow features alone may suffice for classification, rendering deeper features unnecessary.",
    "In such situations, residual modules can preserve essential features in the lower layers, preventing network degradation and improving model performance."
  ]
}